text: Gary Ebbels (born 16 March 1947) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League (VFL) in 1967 and 1968. Ebbels was a physical education teacher in Ballarat at Sebastopol Technical School, later known as Sebastopol College, for 44 years.
